    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="579"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1373.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the Navy</gloss> to
                        Admiral <persName type="to">Caperton</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 20, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department strongly impressed with number Haitians killed. Department feels that
                    a severe lesson has been taught Cacos and believes that a proper patrol can be
                    maintained to preserve order and protect innocent persons without further
                    offensive operations. Should these measures prove inadequate inform Department
                    before taking steps that would lead to loss of life on either side except in
                    case of urgent necessity. Acknowledge.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
